newTreeSet

public static <E> TreeSet<E> newTreeSet(Iterable<? extends E> elements)
Creates a TreeSet containing the elements of the specified iterable. If the iterable is an instance of a SortedSet, PriorityQueue, or SortedCollection, this set will be sorted according to the same ordering. Otherwise, this set will be sorted according to the natural ordering of its elements.

Parameters:
elements - the iterable whose elements are to be placed into this set
Returns:
a TreeSet containing the elements of the specified iterable
